                </td>
                <td align="center" colspan="4" style="background-color:#D9D9D9" rowspan="1"/>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </alternatives>
      </table-wrap>
      <p>Schmeller et al. [<xref rid="pone.0243135.ref013" ref-type="bibr">13</xref>] reviewed different approaches for determining national responsibilities and suggested a standardized method that is freely scalable and can provide an improved basis for setting conservation priorities. The method is also applicable to habitats or ecosystems [<xref rid="pone.0243135.ref007" ref-type="bibr">7</xref>] and comprises three steps (<xref ref-type="fig" rid="pone.0243135.g004">Fig 4</xref>).</p>
      <p>The expected distribution proportion (<italic>DP</italic><sub>exp</sub>) in the focal area is the ratio of the distribution area of a species inside the reference area (<italic>sensu</italic> Schmeller et al. [<xref rid="pone.0243135.ref036" ref-type="bibr">36</xref>, <xref rid="pone.0243135.ref037" ref-type="bibr">37</xref>]) to the total area of the reference area (<xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="pone.0243135.e001">Eq 1</xref>); the observed distribution proportion (<italic>DP</italic><sub>obs</sub>) in the focal area is the ratio of the distribution area of the species in a focal area to the total area of the focal area (<xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="pone.0243135.e002">Eq 2</xref>) [<xref rid="pone.0243135.ref036" ref-type="bibr">36</xref>, <xref rid="pone.0243135.ref037" ref-type="bibr">37</xref>, <xref rid="pone.0243135.ref047" ref-type="bibr">47</xref>].</p>
